, the lamposts that dot the square went ominously dark, and the student loudspeaker played the Internationale, the socialist anthem. At 4 a. The few thousand students remaining in the square stayed calm as they quietly gathered on the steps of the heroes' monument. Troops first entered the square from the south, when a column trotted toward the student encampment about 1 a. The battle for Tiananmen was primarily fought in the streets leading to the square, where scores of people fell trying to prevent columns of troops and armored military vehicles from moving on the students. 